  "title": "Civil & Structural Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Highlight</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>The office is within walking distance of Tai Seng MRT</li>\n  <li>5 days work week</li>\n  <li>Career Growth</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree in Civil &amp; Structural Engineering recognized by PE Board, Singapore</li>\n  <li>A minimum of 1 year of working experience in an engineering consulting company.</li>\n  <li>Competent user of relevant engineering software</li>\n  <li>Effective communication and teamwork abilities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate with a multidisciplinary team to design and develop innovative civil and structural solutions.</li>\n  <li>Preparing civil and structural design calculations/engineering reports</li>\n  <li>Obtaining planning and/or building regulations approval</li>\n  <li>Liaising with relevant government authorities, stakeholders, and project team</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of 3D/FEM design software such as Etabs is an advantage</li>\n  <li>To carry out engineering design according to Eurocodes or relevant informational design codes</li>\n  <li>Carrying out building inspections &amp; reports on findings</li>\n  <li>Attend project meetings with Clients and Consultants from other disciplines</li>\n  <li>To attend site progress meetings and reply to technical queries</li>\n</ul>",
